WEBVTT

00:51.118 --> 00:53.652
<i> [ambient music]</i>

00:53.654 --> 00:55.888
<i> - I've been here before.</i>

00:59.660 --> 01:02.194
<i> Where memories turn on you.</i>

01:05.332 --> 01:07.166
<i> Even the good ones.</i>

01:08.602 --> 01:11.470
- More bad dreams?
- [gasps]

01:11.472 --> 01:15.140
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:15.275 --> 01:17.141
- Maybe you should read
something besides my journals

01:17.143 --> 01:19.211
if they're giving you
nightmares.

01:20.547 --> 01:22.147
- It's comforting to me,
actually,

01:22.282 --> 01:24.416
reading your last words.

01:24.551 --> 01:26.218
- That's nice.

01:26.353 --> 01:33.525
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:38.165 --> 01:40.099
So what is bothering you?

01:44.771 --> 01:47.906
- Just the usual
murder thoughts.

01:50.845 --> 01:53.111
Wishing death on Joseph.

01:53.247 --> 01:57.850
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:57.984 --> 01:59.852
<i> Wilford said the weakest</i>
<i> are those</i>

01:59.986 --> 02:01.253
<i> who suffer from memories.</i>

02:01.388 --> 02:03.655
[rumbling]

02:03.790 --> 02:05.323
<i> [tense music]</i>

02:05.459 --> 02:07.926
<i> The strongest carry the past</i>
<i> like fuel</i>

02:08.062 --> 02:10.128
<i> to ignite a path forward.</i>

02:10.130 --> 02:12.731
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:12.867 --> 02:15.067
- [spits, grunts]

02:17.404 --> 02:19.204
<i> - He wasn't wrong.</i>

02:19.206 --> 02:26.145
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:28.615 --> 02:30.749
- Where are we?

02:32.152 --> 02:33.686
[rumbling]

02:33.820 --> 02:35.687
- We're slowing.
- Yeah.

02:35.822 --> 02:38.490
And here he comes.

02:38.625 --> 02:41.226
[knocks on door]
- Knock, knock.

02:41.361 --> 02:44.697
Rise and shine.
Track blockage.

02:44.831 --> 02:47.632
- Mm, sure do miss him.

02:47.768 --> 02:50.569
- Oh, my God.

02:51.772 --> 02:54.038
- Blockage is about
three kilometers away.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.507
- We're almost
at the main line.

02:55.642 --> 02:57.642
- Why did I take this shortcut?

02:57.778 --> 03:00.079
[monitors beeping]

03:01.782 --> 03:04.316
Jesus.
Looks like train cars.

03:04.451 --> 03:05.951
- What?

03:08.255 --> 03:13.192
- You know what's out there,
don't you?

03:14.328 --> 03:17.195
<i> - My continuous,</i>
<i> inescapable loop.</i>

03:17.331 --> 03:19.331
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:19.466 --> 03:22.735
<i> Our past and future</i>
<i> bound by one track</i>

03:22.869 --> 03:26.138
<i> under the wheels</i>
<i> of Snowpiercer,</i>

03:26.273 --> 03:30.275
<i> 1,029 cars long.</i>

03:30.410 --> 03:33.278
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

03:33.413 --> 03:40.319
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:48.228 --> 03:50.763
- We'll be at New Eden
in less than two weeks,

03:50.897 --> 03:54.366
so if you have any issues
or questions

03:54.501 --> 03:57.836
about transitioning
your departments, I'm here.

03:57.972 --> 04:00.372
- Uh, question for Ms. Asha.

04:00.507 --> 04:03.442
I'm Astrid, food services.
Welcome aboard.

04:03.577 --> 04:04.909
- Thank you.

04:05.045 --> 04:08.180
- How did you manage
before it started warming

04:08.315 --> 04:11.583
when the whole planet
hit deep freeze?

04:11.718 --> 04:14.386
- Uh, what you are calling
New Eden,

04:14.521 --> 04:17.790
the Horn of Africa,
never got as cold as--

04:17.924 --> 04:21.059
- Excuse me.
Hey, up top, hi.

04:21.061 --> 04:23.127
I'm Pike, no vocation.

04:23.129 --> 04:28.067
I was wondering,
were there trees in New Eden?

04:29.003 --> 04:31.203
- There were small trees
and shrubs.

04:31.338 --> 04:35.140
- Oh, were there insects?
- Yes.

04:35.275 --> 04:37.942
There were several kinds
of insects in my hydroponics.

04:38.078 --> 04:39.478
- You're needed in the Engine.
- Good.

04:39.480 --> 04:41.013
Maybe they'll tell me
why we slowed to a crawl.

04:41.148 --> 04:43.415
Okay, I think that's it.
See everyone tomorrow.

04:43.550 --> 04:44.683
[indistinct chatter]

04:44.819 --> 04:46.618
Nicely done.
You good?

04:46.753 --> 04:47.886
- It's been a long time since

04:48.022 --> 04:49.287
I've tried to be
an inspiration.

04:49.423 --> 04:51.223
- Yeah, no worries.
You're doing great.

04:51.358 --> 04:54.026
Tristan has set up some time
for us tonight to catch up.

04:54.161 --> 04:56.495
- Okay.
- Okay, see you then.

04:56.497 --> 04:58.296
<i> [tense music]</i>

04:58.432 --> 05:00.232
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:00.367 --> 05:01.566
You're late.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.768
- You didn't invite me, Layton.

05:03.770 --> 05:07.039
- Like, days late.
We could use you.

05:07.174 --> 05:10.308
- Could you though?
- Stepped up as a leader.

05:10.444 --> 05:12.244
People will look to you
if you let 'em.

05:12.379 --> 05:14.579
- Hmm.

05:14.581 --> 05:16.781
[sighs]

05:16.917 --> 05:20.052
You know, when--
when you were gone,

05:20.187 --> 05:21.253
we lost Mama Grande

05:21.388 --> 05:24.256
and both Last Australians
to the flu.

05:24.391 --> 05:25.858
- I know. I'm sorry.

05:25.992 --> 05:28.694
- And then you show up
and we lose Strong Boy.

05:30.130 --> 05:32.865
- Respect.
May they rest.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.167
- They don't though, do they?

05:37.271 --> 05:39.003
- We have paid dearly, brother,

05:39.005 --> 05:43.409
but we are bringing
the train back to land.

05:44.879 --> 05:46.745
Choose your vocation.

05:46.747 --> 05:48.914
- [scoffs, chuckles]

05:49.884 --> 05:53.052
Wow, I appreciate that.

05:54.621 --> 05:58.957
But it's still you asking, hmm?

05:58.959 --> 06:01.359
The leader who left us.

06:01.361 --> 06:05.964
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:06.100 --> 06:07.699
- Think about it, Pike.

06:07.834 --> 06:09.301
[paper rustles]

06:09.436 --> 06:11.503
Looks like three cars.

06:11.638 --> 06:13.171
They were Big Alice?

06:13.173 --> 06:16.374
- In year one, Wilford cut cars
to lose weight.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.510
I was only ten.

06:18.645 --> 06:21.045
I didn't know that
they were dropped off here.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.380
- How easy are they to move?

06:22.382 --> 06:23.848
- We don't have to
push them far.

06:23.984 --> 06:24.917
There's a siding off
the main track.

06:25.051 --> 06:27.319
- The rail clamps are down.

06:27.454 --> 06:28.520
- Oh, shit.

06:28.655 --> 06:30.589
They've dropped anchor.
[monitor beeps]

06:30.591 --> 06:33.125
- They essentially bolt
the cars to the track.

06:33.260 --> 06:34.659
Once the clamps are down,
there's nothing

06:34.661 --> 06:35.928
you can do to move them.

06:36.063 --> 06:37.796
- What's the alternative?
- Back to the main line,

06:37.932 --> 06:41.133
down through the Oceania Loop.
23 days.

06:41.268 --> 06:42.667
- Can't afford a delay
like that.

06:42.803 --> 06:44.469
- It'll give people a chance
to catch up with the lie.

06:44.605 --> 06:46.338
- Yeah, Asha's already
struggling with it.

06:46.473 --> 06:48.406
- All right.
So we board the cars,

06:48.408 --> 06:51.143
fire up the systems,
disengage the clamps.

06:51.278 --> 06:52.677
Be tricky.
Years of ice buildup.

06:52.679 --> 06:54.346
- I'll go.

06:54.481 --> 06:56.348
What?
I know the cars best.

06:56.483 --> 06:57.882
I'll take a couple RF batteries
and I'll be in...

06:58.018 --> 07:00.018
- Alice?
- And out in a few hours. Ben.

07:00.154 --> 07:02.321
- That's a two-Engineer job
at best.

07:03.490 --> 07:05.758
I'll go with you.
Javi can drive.

07:05.892 --> 07:08.360
He'll just need to reverse
to keep the systems running

07:08.495 --> 07:10.895
until it's time
to come push the cars off.

07:10.897 --> 07:12.364
He needs to get back
in the saddle.

07:12.499 --> 07:14.098
- It's either Javi
or we backtrack.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.301
- We're not backtracking.
- As I thought.

07:16.303 --> 07:18.971
I'll prepare the sled.

07:19.105 --> 07:21.439
[door whooshes]

07:21.441 --> 07:23.308
- Look, I know your friend's
going through

07:23.310 --> 07:24.977
a rough time or whatever,

07:25.111 --> 07:27.379
but this couch is starting
to smell like him.

07:28.649 --> 07:29.848
[glass bangs]
- Jesus.

07:29.984 --> 07:32.250
Okay, come on.
- [grunts]

07:32.252 --> 07:34.519
I-I got it.
- Where'd everybody go?

07:34.655 --> 07:37.456
- Okay, come on, boss.
Duty calls.

07:37.591 --> 07:38.590
- [grumbles]

07:38.725 --> 07:40.659
[rumbling]

07:40.661 --> 07:42.127
Bess, you're a good friend.

07:42.262 --> 07:45.063
- You know, your daughter's
struggling, too,

07:45.065 --> 07:46.465
and pissing off the neighbors.

07:46.467 --> 07:48.400
- It's good. She's good.
I got it.

07:48.535 --> 07:50.735
[loud rock music playing]
Hey, firecracker.

07:50.871 --> 07:52.737
- Where'd you find him?
Compost?

07:52.873 --> 07:54.473
- Hey, watch it.

07:54.608 --> 07:56.008
Where do you think
you're backpacking?

07:56.143 --> 07:57.742
- Why? You don't care.

07:57.878 --> 08:00.913
Just go pass out in a pile
of Mum's stuff again.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.483
- Carly, I'm sorry.

08:04.618 --> 08:06.618
There's just this--
like, this hole in me.

08:06.753 --> 08:09.254
- You're not the only one
it happened to!

08:10.957 --> 08:13.558
<i> [tense tone]</i>

08:13.560 --> 08:15.427
- Carly, I know
you're going through a lot.

08:15.562 --> 08:17.095
He just needs help
getting back--

08:17.097 --> 08:18.963
- Then you do it!

08:18.965 --> 08:21.966
<i> [ambient, somber music]</i>

08:21.968 --> 08:23.968
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:24.104 --> 08:26.905
- Hey. Might not mean much now,

08:26.907 --> 08:30.375
but you will get through this
and I'm gonna help you.

08:30.511 --> 08:33.978
- People think Anne died
in her sleep, Bess.

08:33.980 --> 08:37.916
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:37.918 --> 08:41.119
The drawers aren't sleep.

08:41.255 --> 08:43.655
I need to be where she died.

08:43.790 --> 08:46.725
Can you take me there?

08:46.727 --> 08:49.395
Please?

08:54.601 --> 08:57.936
- Batteries full, check.

08:59.206 --> 09:02.274
- Maybe pack an extra battery?
Better safe than--

09:02.409 --> 09:03.742
- Walking into the cold

09:03.878 --> 09:06.411
and freezing to death
nowhere to be found?

09:06.547 --> 09:11.016
- Hey, why are you doing this?

09:12.553 --> 09:15.353
- Track needs to be cleared.
It's routine, isn't it?

09:15.489 --> 09:18.257
- No.
It's anything but.

09:20.294 --> 09:22.627
You aren't responsible
for his sins, Alex.

09:22.763 --> 09:25.630
<i> [tense, ambient music]</i>

09:25.766 --> 09:32.538
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:39.513 --> 09:41.113
- [indistinct]

09:41.248 --> 09:44.116
<i> [music intensifies]</i>

09:44.251 --> 09:47.051
[breathes deeply]

09:47.187 --> 09:49.854
[air whooshes]

09:49.856 --> 09:51.856
- You good?
- I'm good.

09:51.858 --> 09:54.593
- Snowpiercer, Snowpiercer,
suits are sealed.

09:54.728 --> 09:57.029
- Braking to a full stop.

09:58.132 --> 10:00.865
[metal screeches]

10:01.001 --> 10:04.403
- Stopped.
Finally.

10:04.538 --> 10:07.806
We've rolled up on something.

10:07.942 --> 10:09.674
- Who are you talking to?

10:09.676 --> 10:12.611
- My favorite thinking partner.
- Yourself?

10:12.746 --> 10:15.381
- [chuckles]
Yes.

10:17.017 --> 10:20.885
- So what's your cave painting
say?

10:21.021 --> 10:25.223
Looks like you have it
narrowed down to, um--to Asia?

10:25.359 --> 10:26.691
- It's hard to keep track
of every turn.

10:26.827 --> 10:28.093
I have to sleep sometimes.

10:28.228 --> 10:30.695
- Sure. Poor thing.

10:30.697 --> 10:34.366
- I know.
My hands throbs constantly

10:34.501 --> 10:36.568
and, uh--and I'm only
allowed a spoon.

10:36.703 --> 10:38.637
- Mm.

10:38.773 --> 10:40.973
[rumbling]

10:41.107 --> 10:43.709
- They're reversing now.

10:45.980 --> 10:48.647
I think they dropped off
a clearing crew.

10:48.649 --> 10:50.582
Backing off now
to let them work.

10:50.717 --> 10:53.185
[chuckles]

10:55.389 --> 10:58.122
I know exactly where we are.

10:58.124 --> 11:01.059
[laughs]

11:01.061 --> 11:03.261
[loud rumbling]

11:03.263 --> 11:06.264
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

11:06.266 --> 11:13.172
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:17.144 --> 11:20.312
[metal clanking]

11:27.554 --> 11:30.222
- We need to get inside.
Let's get this started.

11:30.357 --> 11:37.329
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:40.901 --> 11:42.834
- Can you describe it
to me again?

11:42.836 --> 11:46.372
- A tree big enough
to live in,

11:46.506 --> 11:50.175
leaves on every branch,

11:50.310 --> 11:53.779
and the light.

11:53.914 --> 11:56.448
Zarah, it was alive.

11:56.584 --> 11:59.651
<i> [tranquil music]</i>

11:59.787 --> 12:02.520
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:02.656 --> 12:05.457
I don't know
how I know it's real.

12:05.459 --> 12:09.928
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:09.930 --> 12:12.498
Now I sold Asha on it.

12:17.071 --> 12:18.904
What if I'm wrong?

12:21.741 --> 12:23.409
- What if you're right?

12:23.543 --> 12:29.448
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:33.153 --> 12:36.822
- Just get up here.
That's right. Just there.

12:38.025 --> 12:39.825
Find out how we move the sled,
Alex.

12:39.960 --> 12:41.226
- Okay.

12:41.361 --> 12:42.828
- Steady.
- Got it?

12:42.963 --> 12:44.029
- Yup.

12:44.164 --> 12:46.298
[both panting]

12:47.768 --> 12:49.368
Three RFBs.

12:50.638 --> 12:52.370
Are you planning to spend
the night here?

12:52.506 --> 12:53.705
- You're always trying
to bond with me.

12:53.707 --> 12:55.040
I'd figured I'd give you
a chance.

12:55.175 --> 12:58.243
- I do like adventure camping.

12:58.378 --> 12:59.845
Stay close.

12:59.980 --> 13:01.513
<i> [light, eerie music]</i>

13:01.649 --> 13:05.517
Snowpiercer, we are in.

13:05.653 --> 13:07.585
- Copy, clearing crew.

13:07.721 --> 13:10.255
<i> - Heading to the first panel.</i>

13:10.390 --> 13:13.125
- [speaking Spanish]

13:13.260 --> 13:16.128
[both panting]

13:16.263 --> 13:22.734
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:22.870 --> 13:24.803
- Alex.

13:29.076 --> 13:31.877
- Please tell him why
you're really here.

13:42.890 --> 13:45.491
- You okay?

13:45.625 --> 13:47.359
- Yeah.

13:47.495 --> 13:51.897
- All right.
Let's get jacked in.

13:52.032 --> 13:54.632
[saw whirring]

13:54.634 --> 13:56.634
<i> [upbeat electronic music</i>
<i> playing]</i>

13:56.770 --> 13:59.638
- Ah, that's about right.

14:01.441 --> 14:04.176
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:04.311 --> 14:07.245
Yep, that's me.

14:07.381 --> 14:08.580
Lovely. Thanks.

14:08.582 --> 14:10.582
[door whooshes]

14:16.190 --> 14:19.725
Well, well, well,
that's a sight for sore eyes.

14:19.860 --> 14:22.594
All dressed up.
What's the occasion?

14:22.730 --> 14:25.063
- In your first month
below zero,

14:25.065 --> 14:26.765
I made you a promise.

14:28.869 --> 14:30.802
Remember?

14:30.938 --> 14:33.539
- No. Have you got a banana?

14:33.673 --> 14:37.609
- And I intend to keep
my promise, right?

14:37.611 --> 14:40.879
Something about
if we made it through...

14:41.014 --> 14:43.449
- That we would share
Bananas Foster.

14:44.552 --> 14:48.153
- Yeah. So how about it?

14:48.288 --> 14:49.821
- What, now?
- Yeah.

14:49.957 --> 14:51.757
- Right now?

14:51.892 --> 14:53.425
It's my first shift
back in the morning.

14:53.561 --> 14:55.227
I've got so much to do tonight.

14:55.362 --> 14:56.762
- Pardon my observating,

14:56.897 --> 14:59.898
but you don't seem
too thrilled with that.

15:00.033 --> 15:01.700
- No.

15:03.571 --> 15:05.103
- [in nasally voice]
Bananas.

15:05.105 --> 15:08.807
Come on.
Just one last hurrah, okay?

15:09.977 --> 15:11.477
- Mm.

15:12.580 --> 15:15.447
[people chattering]

15:15.583 --> 15:17.382
<i> [unsettling tone]</i>

15:17.517 --> 15:19.451
- [exhales sharply]

15:19.453 --> 15:20.518
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:20.654 --> 15:21.587
[gasps]

15:21.721 --> 15:23.121
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:23.123 --> 15:25.024
[plates clatter]

15:27.061 --> 15:29.261
- Sorry.

15:29.396 --> 15:31.663
- Why are you sorry?

15:31.665 --> 15:33.665
- I, uh...

15:33.801 --> 15:35.734
I still feel guilty
eating beef.

15:35.869 --> 15:37.402
- Is that, like,
a religious thing?

15:37.537 --> 15:39.871
- Oh, more of a fear of
disappointing my grandmother.

15:40.007 --> 15:43.208
- That's mutton,
if that changes anything.

15:43.343 --> 15:45.143
Unfortunately,
cows are extinct.

15:45.279 --> 15:47.145
- I thought everything
was extinct.

15:47.147 --> 15:48.414
- Yeah.

15:51.351 --> 15:55.487
Hey, take it slow.

15:57.425 --> 15:59.692
- Thank you. I'll try.

16:03.097 --> 16:05.030
- Oh.

16:05.165 --> 16:06.965
Aren't you very
"Spy vs. Spy."

16:06.967 --> 16:09.701
- Not sure if you're aware,
but I was sidelined

16:09.837 --> 16:11.503
for most of Zarah's pregnancy.

16:11.505 --> 16:13.238
- I was not aware of that.

16:13.373 --> 16:15.373
- Dr. Headwood took over
shortly after you left.

16:15.509 --> 16:17.242
I've been snooping.

16:17.377 --> 16:19.511
<i> [tense music]</i>

16:19.647 --> 16:23.048
- Ixodes scapularis protein.

16:23.183 --> 16:24.450
Leptin receptor?

16:24.584 --> 16:25.984
Does any of this mean
anything to you?

16:25.986 --> 16:27.719
- My skills got stuck
in a war zone, so barely,

16:27.855 --> 16:30.489
but it's about gene therapy.

16:32.126 --> 16:36.194
Some of those processes
are in Josie's file too

16:36.196 --> 16:37.696
for cold treatment.

16:39.533 --> 16:41.533
I thought you better know.

16:41.535 --> 16:44.470
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:45.739 --> 16:48.006
- All right, well,
we're jacked in.

16:48.008 --> 16:51.409
Ready for power. There she is.

16:51.411 --> 16:55.747
Snowpiercer, Snowpiercer,
first panel is live.

16:55.749 --> 16:58.117
<i> - Do you copy, Snowpiercer?</i>

17:00.220 --> 17:03.155
<i> Javi, we're moving</i>
<i> to the next panel.</i>

17:05.359 --> 17:07.292
[dog growls]

17:07.427 --> 17:09.795
- [breath shaking]

17:11.031 --> 17:13.431
<i> Do you copy?</i>
<i> [dog barks]</i>

17:13.567 --> 17:16.568
- Uh, copy that.
Uh, Standing by.

17:16.570 --> 17:18.036
- Javi's not ready
to drive yet.

17:18.172 --> 17:21.707
- He'll be fine.
Let's just keep it calm.

17:22.976 --> 17:25.443
- Ben, there's something I
probably should have told you.

17:25.445 --> 17:27.112
- Oh, yeah? What's that?

17:27.247 --> 17:29.048
- Don't freak out.

17:30.317 --> 17:32.051
- Oh.

17:37.858 --> 17:40.325
What is this?

17:40.460 --> 17:41.960
- It's Wilford's cull.

17:43.397 --> 17:47.032
Those he sacrificed
to keep the rest of us alive.

17:48.602 --> 17:51.804
[both panting]

17:54.474 --> 17:55.807
- Why didn't you tell me?

17:55.943 --> 17:58.344
- If I had,
would you have let me come?

17:58.478 --> 18:00.612
- I'm already relying
on one fragile Engineer.

18:00.748 --> 18:02.480
Now I have to worry about two.

18:02.616 --> 18:05.617
- He'll be fine.
- I'm serious, Engineer.

18:05.753 --> 18:07.353
I have to abort this
if you're losing it.

18:07.487 --> 18:09.821
- I'm not.

18:09.823 --> 18:11.790
It's my story.

18:13.293 --> 18:15.794
I just had to
see it for myself.

18:17.431 --> 18:19.030
- Any other surprises?

18:19.032 --> 18:22.167
'Cause the next panel
is all the way up there.

18:22.302 --> 18:24.737
- I hope not.

18:29.243 --> 18:31.443
<i> [eerie tone]</i>

18:31.445 --> 18:34.847
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:36.850 --> 18:39.918
<i> [melancholy piano music]</i>

18:39.920 --> 18:42.921
<i> [muffled chatter, laughter]</i>

18:42.923 --> 18:50.062
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:01.809 --> 19:04.209
- He did it in their sleep?

19:05.145 --> 19:08.080
- It's the only way to kill
half of your crew.

19:10.150 --> 19:14.886
The middle of the night
when nobody's expecting it.

19:14.888 --> 19:22.061
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:35.575 --> 19:39.911
He tested us all for stamina,
physical strength.

19:39.913 --> 19:43.181
He ranked us by skillset.

19:43.183 --> 19:46.085
Used Book Club
to find the original thinkers.

19:47.587 --> 19:49.921
He deemed us The Essentials.

19:50.057 --> 19:52.524
Families were divided.

19:52.660 --> 19:55.927
Couples were separated.

19:55.929 --> 19:59.131
- Made you feel chosen,
didn't he?

20:01.601 --> 20:03.669
- I was chosen.
<i> - Alex.</i>

20:03.803 --> 20:05.537
<i> [door squeaks]</i>
<i> - His crew.</i>

20:05.673 --> 20:07.405
- Alex.

20:07.407 --> 20:09.407
Alex, Alex, wake up.

20:09.543 --> 20:12.077
Alex. Come on, come on.

20:12.212 --> 20:13.679
Come on.

20:13.813 --> 20:17.282
- Loyal. He's good at that.

20:18.952 --> 20:20.418
- I'll go set that up.

20:20.554 --> 20:22.020
- You know what
happens now, Alex?

20:22.156 --> 20:23.689
- You have to blow ice
off of the clamps.

20:23.824 --> 20:25.491
- No, I have to leave you
alone in here,

20:25.625 --> 20:27.126
so look me in the eyes.

20:31.631 --> 20:35.000
- Thank you, Ben. Got it.

20:36.103 --> 20:39.771
- Stay in my ear.
Walk it through.

20:39.773 --> 20:41.940
- My favorite thing.

20:46.914 --> 20:48.847
- Do you know
where she is?

20:48.849 --> 20:51.649
<i> [dark, ambient music]</i>

20:51.651 --> 20:52.784
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:52.920 --> 20:54.953
- I think so.

21:00.427 --> 21:03.294
<i> [ominous music]</i>

21:03.430 --> 21:06.097
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:06.099 --> 21:08.500
- This is where you were.

21:08.635 --> 21:10.869
Anne is in that drawer.

21:14.441 --> 21:19.244
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:19.380 --> 21:20.779
- Can you give me a minute,
please?

21:20.914 --> 21:22.881
- Of course.

21:25.986 --> 21:28.720
- [breathes deeply]

21:28.722 --> 21:35.861
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:46.874 --> 21:49.941
<i> [up-tempo dance music</i>
<i> playing]</i>

21:49.943 --> 21:56.915
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:10.631 --> 22:12.831
- It's on the house.

22:12.966 --> 22:14.499
- Thank you.

22:14.635 --> 22:17.703
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:17.838 --> 22:20.972
[loud chatter]

22:21.108 --> 22:24.843
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:24.978 --> 22:26.978
- Hey. I'm done dealing with

22:26.980 --> 22:29.514
your free pour victims all day,
all right?

22:29.650 --> 22:31.983
- You like it just fine
when it's your glass.

22:31.985 --> 22:33.719
- Go easy on her.

22:33.854 --> 22:36.721
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:36.723 --> 22:39.390
<i> [whirring]</i>

22:39.526 --> 22:45.931
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:54.875 --> 22:56.275
- Hey, you're
the New Eden girl.

22:56.410 --> 22:59.478
- Huh?
- What's it like outside?

22:59.613 --> 23:01.346
- Green.
- [laughs]

23:01.482 --> 23:03.148
Oh, that's awesome.

23:03.150 --> 23:05.550
<i> [unsettling tone]</i>

23:05.686 --> 23:08.620
<i> [dance music continues]</i>

23:08.622 --> 23:14.927
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:17.898 --> 23:20.632
<i> [unsettling tone]</i>

23:20.767 --> 23:27.539
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:33.180 --> 23:37.649
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:37.651 --> 23:40.852
- [breathing heavily]

23:40.988 --> 23:43.455
<i> [unsettling tone]</i>

23:43.590 --> 23:44.589
<i> [dance music]</i>

23:44.725 --> 23:46.391
- [grunts]

23:46.393 --> 23:48.459
- [screams]

23:48.461 --> 23:49.594
[sobs]

23:49.730 --> 23:51.330
[both grunting]

23:51.464 --> 23:52.597
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:52.599 --> 23:55.066
<i> [high-pitched tone]</i>

23:55.068 --> 23:57.336
[breathing heavily]

23:57.470 --> 23:59.071
- Asha.

24:00.741 --> 24:02.474
It's Till.

24:02.609 --> 24:05.978
Sorry, you looked
a little lost out there.

24:08.882 --> 24:12.851
- Who I was, how I got here...

24:15.022 --> 24:16.822
I don't think I
was worth saving.

24:16.957 --> 24:19.090
- No.

24:19.226 --> 24:21.960
We all feel that guilt.

24:22.095 --> 24:23.695
- I might implode.

24:23.831 --> 24:26.565
- Listen, I know you got a lot
of pressure on you right now--

24:26.700 --> 24:29.535
- Don't worry.
I won't spill the lie.

24:32.105 --> 24:35.240
I can see what an Eden does
for their souls.

24:36.443 --> 24:40.112
- If you get that,
then you're one of us.

24:43.184 --> 24:45.517
Come on.

24:45.652 --> 24:48.487
Let me take you back
to your quarters.

24:50.924 --> 24:52.591
[device beeps]

24:52.726 --> 24:55.394
[wind howling]

24:55.529 --> 24:56.996
[rapid beeping]
- Fire in the hole!

24:57.130 --> 24:59.664
[explosion booms, rumbles]

24:59.800 --> 25:01.332
- Disturbing the dead, Ben.

25:01.468 --> 25:04.135
- Tell them I'm sorry.
Halfway there.

25:04.137 --> 25:05.871
Two clamps to go.

25:07.140 --> 25:09.274
You all right in there?
- I'm okay.

25:09.276 --> 25:11.943
Okay, panel two is set.
<i> - Copy that.</i>

25:11.945 --> 25:13.545
- You ready?

25:13.680 --> 25:16.548
<i> [ominous ambient music]</i>

25:16.683 --> 25:23.155
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:25.826 --> 25:27.926
What was her name?

25:29.630 --> 25:31.397
- Shilo.

25:34.101 --> 25:35.901
[door squeaks]

25:35.903 --> 25:42.173
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:42.175 --> 25:44.243
You know, for all the people
I've lost,

25:44.377 --> 25:47.178
I've ever seen
anybody's dead body.

25:47.180 --> 25:51.216
Not Shilo's, not Grandma...

25:52.653 --> 25:54.620
Not Grandpa.

25:56.724 --> 25:58.957
Not you.

26:04.197 --> 26:09.000
- Reality isn't necessarily
kinder than our imaginations.

26:09.136 --> 26:13.404
- Mom, I'm ready.

26:13.406 --> 26:15.674
- Alice, wake up. That's it.

26:15.809 --> 26:18.543
Alex. Come on, come on.

26:18.545 --> 26:25.517
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:39.766 --> 26:46.672
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:49.376 --> 26:53.044
[metal screeches]

26:53.046 --> 26:55.280
- Still reversing.

26:57.784 --> 27:01.052
Feels like Javier is driving,
don't you think?

27:01.054 --> 27:03.455
Bit hesitant.

27:03.590 --> 27:05.324
- It does kinda.

27:06.994 --> 27:08.860
- That means--

27:08.862 --> 27:12.397
Oh, no. That means, uh,

27:12.399 --> 27:15.300
Alex is out there
with the bodies.

27:17.470 --> 27:22.041
- Yes, she is.
- I'm sorry. Truly.

27:23.877 --> 27:25.076
Her friend, Shilo.

27:25.212 --> 27:27.546
No one should
have to revisit that

27:29.082 --> 27:30.649
[sighs]

27:32.419 --> 27:34.586
- We wouldn't listen
to music together.

27:36.223 --> 27:38.890
We would listen to this.

27:38.892 --> 27:41.627
Try to remember
life before the train.

27:45.298 --> 27:48.167
<i> [insects chirping,</i>
<i> water flowing]</i>

27:48.301 --> 27:51.036
<i> [birds calling]</i>

27:51.038 --> 27:53.505
<i> [frogs croaking]</i>

27:58.579 --> 28:01.847
<i> [emotional atmospheric music]</i>

28:01.849 --> 28:04.850
<i> [nature sounds continue]</i>

28:04.852 --> 28:10.121
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:10.257 --> 28:11.523
- I can't remember.

28:11.658 --> 28:14.593
- Works better if you
close your eyes.

28:17.865 --> 28:20.131
<i> [seagulls calling]</i>

28:20.267 --> 28:22.868
<i> [waves crashing]</i>

28:23.003 --> 28:29.608
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:29.743 --> 28:32.378
[girls giggling]

28:48.962 --> 28:51.230
- Prenatal gene therapy.
- [gasps] Oh, my goodness.

28:51.364 --> 28:53.232
[chuckles] You scared me.

28:55.302 --> 28:57.569
- I haven't begun.

28:57.571 --> 29:01.440
- Uh, well, Mr. Layton,

29:01.575 --> 29:03.508
you're going to be
a new father.

29:03.510 --> 29:06.377
It's not, um, surprising
that you have some concerns.

29:06.379 --> 29:10.315
- You experimented
on my unborn child!

29:10.317 --> 29:11.850
- Yes, yes, yes, we did.

29:11.985 --> 29:13.652
Wilford had us do, uh,

29:13.787 --> 29:15.987
enhanced genetic code
treatment.

29:15.989 --> 29:18.123
Please! It's a--it's a gift.

29:18.125 --> 29:19.724
My treatments are gonna work.

29:19.726 --> 29:21.460
- What about our consent?
- My God!

29:21.595 --> 29:23.729
You what? Yeah, okay.

29:23.864 --> 29:25.196
You need to--
you need to talk to Zarah.

29:25.332 --> 29:26.465
- Why?

29:26.600 --> 29:28.066
- Just talk to the mother
of your child.

29:28.201 --> 29:30.235
<i> [chilling music]</i>

29:33.540 --> 29:35.740
<i> [lively music playing]</i>

29:35.876 --> 29:37.609
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:37.744 --> 29:40.479
<i> [singing in Spanish]</i>

29:40.614 --> 29:42.280
- That's real vanilla
ice cream.

29:42.282 --> 29:44.583
- Stolen from the children.

29:53.293 --> 29:55.360
- Mmm. Mmm.

29:55.496 --> 29:58.897
- [chuckles]
- Mmm.

29:58.899 --> 30:02.601
Well, I know who you were
in the old world, Mr. Pike.

30:04.238 --> 30:05.770
- Oh. Who?

30:05.772 --> 30:08.507
- You were a chef
with a Michelin star bistro

30:08.509 --> 30:10.509
serving only Bananas Foster.

30:10.511 --> 30:12.577
[both laugh]

30:12.579 --> 30:14.913
- Busted. [laughs]

30:15.049 --> 30:16.915
Mmm.

30:18.785 --> 30:22.320
- What were you then?
Come on. Seriously.

30:22.322 --> 30:24.056
- What?

30:26.660 --> 30:29.794
- Oh, no one gets to know
who you were before. No?

30:29.796 --> 30:33.032
Okay. Fine.
So who are you gonna be?

30:34.535 --> 30:37.269
- Just Pike.
Hustling and scuffling.

30:37.404 --> 30:38.537
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

30:38.672 --> 30:40.605
- You can't take Layton
up on his offer?

30:40.607 --> 30:42.741
Can't choose a path?

30:42.877 --> 30:46.478
We need leaders like you,
you know? Hmm?

30:47.682 --> 30:50.883
- It's my curse, Ruth.
I can't rah rah.

30:51.017 --> 30:52.484
I can't kumbaya.

30:52.619 --> 30:54.553
- Oh, but you can last hurrah?

30:57.291 --> 31:00.092
- For you, anything.

31:00.227 --> 31:04.963
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:04.965 --> 31:06.965
[metal clanging]

31:07.101 --> 31:09.802
[wind howling]

31:12.707 --> 31:14.706
[rapid beeping]
- Fire in the hole.

31:14.841 --> 31:16.842
[explosion booms, rumbles]

31:18.979 --> 31:21.613
<i> All right, Alex,</i>
<i> that's the last one.</i>

31:23.384 --> 31:24.783
<i> Your turn.</i>

31:24.919 --> 31:28.186
- Copy.
Disengaging rail clamps.

31:28.188 --> 31:30.856
[mechanical whirring]

31:32.126 --> 31:33.858
- No movement.

31:33.860 --> 31:37.262
- I-I know. I just signaled it.

31:37.264 --> 31:38.931
- What's going on guys?
Am I coming back?

31:39.065 --> 31:41.333
- We have to troubleshoot
this, Ben.

31:41.468 --> 31:44.869
- Negative, Javi.
Hold your roll.

31:44.871 --> 31:49.375
Run a second discharge sequence
and you better call Layton.

31:51.011 --> 31:52.544
<i> [tense tone]</i>
- [winces]

31:52.679 --> 31:56.281
<i> [dog barks. growls]</i>

31:56.416 --> 31:58.417
[phone rings]
- Adapt or die.

31:58.552 --> 32:00.485
Just like the Tail used to say.

32:00.487 --> 32:01.820
- Headwood's treatment
is experimental.

32:01.822 --> 32:04.823
You consented
to risking her life.

32:04.825 --> 32:06.891
- You risked all of our lives.

32:06.893 --> 32:10.028
I made a decision
just like you without me.

32:10.164 --> 32:12.230
- What about her consent?
- What about her consent?

32:12.232 --> 32:14.767
I'm her mother.
I gave her an advantage

32:14.901 --> 32:17.502
because her father
is taking us outside.

32:17.638 --> 32:20.038
- Uh-uh. Stop that shit.
Don't you put this on me.

32:20.174 --> 32:22.641
This wasn't for me.
This wasn't for her.

32:22.777 --> 32:25.109
This was one of your
calculated moves

32:25.111 --> 32:26.979
to guarantee
your own protection.

32:27.114 --> 32:29.314
- Well, you weren't here.

32:29.449 --> 32:31.716
You're not here, are you?

32:31.718 --> 32:33.318
We are not a nuclear family.

32:33.320 --> 32:35.187
We're just trying to hold off
the end of the world.

32:35.322 --> 32:37.589
- She was untouched.

32:37.724 --> 32:40.192
And you stamped her
with Wilford!

32:40.327 --> 32:42.795
<i> [somber music]</i>

32:42.929 --> 32:45.464
- Well, I guess you have
a choice to make.

32:45.599 --> 32:48.266
You can either get over it

32:48.268 --> 32:51.403
or carry it around
like a millstone forever.

32:51.538 --> 32:56.341
Me and Wilford
and all that rage.

32:56.477 --> 32:58.343
<i> [tense music]</i>

32:58.479 --> 33:01.079
[phone ringing]

33:01.215 --> 33:07.085
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:07.087 --> 33:09.154
What?

33:11.492 --> 33:14.526
They need you in the Engine.

33:15.629 --> 33:18.697
<i> [sultry electronic music]</i>

33:18.699 --> 33:24.969
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:24.971 --> 33:28.440
- Uh, what's all this?

33:28.575 --> 33:30.108
- This is one of my homes.

33:30.110 --> 33:33.512
- You have a pied-à-terre
in the market?

33:33.647 --> 33:34.646
- Yeah.

33:34.781 --> 33:36.515
- Huh.

33:36.517 --> 33:41.720
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:41.856 --> 33:45.390
Mr. Metrosexual.
- [chuckles]

33:45.526 --> 33:47.793
- I like it.
- Thanks.

33:49.796 --> 33:53.899
- No view, but the amenities?
Mmm.

33:56.737 --> 34:01.406
You're gonna miss your shift,
Ms. Wardell.

34:01.542 --> 34:04.009
- Well, I didn't miss it yet.

34:04.879 --> 34:07.746
<i> [atmospheric music]</i>

34:07.882 --> 34:15.020
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:34.308 --> 34:40.979
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:41.115 --> 34:44.817
- Why do you have an aversion
to potential?

34:50.791 --> 34:54.660
- The best version of me
is already gone, Ruth.

34:59.866 --> 35:03.602
My right hand
to your rebel commander.

35:07.007 --> 35:11.243
You should be leading
this train, not Layton.

35:14.749 --> 35:17.149
- Don't say things like that.

35:17.284 --> 35:24.256
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:25.826 --> 35:28.827
- Okay. Summarize for me, Ben.
Javi's showing me pictures.

35:28.829 --> 35:31.296
<i> - I think we have a block in</i>
<i> the hydraulic ferrofluid line.</i>

35:31.431 --> 35:34.032
The only problem
is there's over 1,000 feet

35:34.034 --> 35:35.433
of line on these cars.

35:35.435 --> 35:36.969
<i> - That could take days</i>
<i> to locate.</i>

35:37.103 --> 35:38.370
<i> I better start back now</i>

35:38.505 --> 35:40.372
<i> before our reserves</i>
<i> reach critical.</i>

35:40.507 --> 35:42.174
- Okay, you guys,
I have a theory.

35:42.309 --> 35:44.309
One of these cars was a lemon.
It was always breaking down.

35:44.444 --> 35:46.244
<i> That's why Wilford</i>
<i> dropped it here.</i>

35:46.246 --> 35:47.980
- So what? You think he knows
where the line is blocked?

35:48.115 --> 35:50.182
- Wilford. Man, it never ends.

35:50.317 --> 35:51.650
- Trust me,
I didn't want to have to

35:51.786 --> 35:53.786
ask for his help either.

35:53.920 --> 35:56.121
- Okay. I'm going to patch him
through from his cell, Ben.

35:56.256 --> 35:58.957
<i> - Terrific. I can hardly wait.</i>

36:00.460 --> 36:02.594
- Hold fast, Engineer.

36:02.729 --> 36:05.597
<i> [dark, tense music]</i>

36:05.732 --> 36:12.805
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:28.823 --> 36:30.622
- Lead Brakeman.

36:30.757 --> 36:32.624
- Michael,
you're relieved here.

36:32.759 --> 36:34.158
- I was told
I was on guard all night.

36:34.160 --> 36:36.761
- I know,
but you're relieved now.

36:36.763 --> 36:38.263
Keys, please.

36:40.967 --> 36:42.434
Thank you.
Have a good night.

36:42.569 --> 36:44.569
- You too, sir. Thank you.

36:44.705 --> 36:51.677
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:52.979 --> 36:54.646
[lock clicks]

36:54.781 --> 36:56.781
- [chuckles] You see, Mel?

36:56.917 --> 36:59.451
I told you they'd come begging.

36:59.586 --> 37:01.053
- [grunting]

37:01.188 --> 37:05.590
- Ah, Lead Brakeman Roche.

37:05.726 --> 37:07.992
Not the supplicant
I was expecting,

37:08.128 --> 37:11.663
but it's good to see you up
and about just the same.

37:11.798 --> 37:13.065
[grunts]

37:13.200 --> 37:16.601
So can't get the clamps off,
eh?

37:16.737 --> 37:19.071
Now you got a team outside

37:19.206 --> 37:23.142
and no way around
but through me.

37:24.144 --> 37:25.944
Oh, come on, Mr. Roche.

37:25.946 --> 37:28.213
Suspension can't be that bad,
can it?

37:28.215 --> 37:31.216
- You tell me.
- [grunts in pain]

37:31.218 --> 37:34.887
You shot it--
you shot it in my heart.

37:35.021 --> 37:37.890
<i> [dark, tense music]</i>

37:38.024 --> 37:40.425
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:40.427 --> 37:42.494
What did you do?

37:44.899 --> 37:47.232
Why did you do that?

37:47.367 --> 37:49.167
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:49.169 --> 37:52.571
Ahh. Ahh.

37:52.706 --> 37:55.841
[groans weakly]

37:57.511 --> 37:59.511
Help me, Mel.

37:59.646 --> 38:01.246
Help me.

38:01.381 --> 38:04.917
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:17.864 --> 38:20.733
<i> [tense, ambient music]</i>

38:20.867 --> 38:22.334
- [coughing]

38:22.469 --> 38:25.670
- What? What happened?
- A dose of his own medicine.

38:25.672 --> 38:28.473
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

38:28.609 --> 38:29.741
Hey, listen, asshole.

38:29.876 --> 38:31.276
I would love to pull up a chair

38:31.278 --> 38:33.478
and watch you die,
but I will save you

38:33.614 --> 38:35.280
if you tell me
what I need to know, okay?

38:35.415 --> 38:37.282
Roche, get on the phone
with the Engine.

38:37.417 --> 38:40.352
- You found the cull.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

38:40.487 --> 38:42.420
We don't know how to release
the real clamps, okay?

38:42.422 --> 38:44.689
I need you to get on the line
with the Engineers.

38:44.825 --> 38:45.758
Roche!

38:45.892 --> 38:48.994
- How is Zarah and our child?

38:50.030 --> 38:52.897
- You will never get between me
and my daughter!

38:53.033 --> 38:54.499
- [groans]

38:54.635 --> 38:57.636
- What the hell happened?
- Get him out of here, please.

38:57.772 --> 39:00.973
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:01.107 --> 39:02.441
And get Dr. Pelton!

39:02.576 --> 39:04.376
- Jesus, Roche.

39:04.511 --> 39:07.579
- [panting]

39:07.714 --> 39:09.047
<i> - Engineer.</i>

39:09.183 --> 39:10.783
- Wilford is no longer
an option.

39:10.917 --> 39:13.385
<i> - Okay.</i>
- Abort the mission.

39:13.520 --> 39:15.788
Go back to pick up
Alex and Ben.

39:15.922 --> 39:19.858
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:19.860 --> 39:24.129
- Clearing crew, no solution.
Snowpiercer is turning back.

39:24.264 --> 39:26.931
<i> ETA on the pickup</i>
<i> is 25 minutes.</i>

39:27.067 --> 39:28.933
- What?

39:28.935 --> 39:30.669
<i> [dog barks]</i>

39:30.805 --> 39:33.138
No, Ben, you have to tell them
that we need more time.

39:33.273 --> 39:35.007
I can do this.

39:35.142 --> 39:36.675
- God damn it.

39:36.811 --> 39:40.078
<i> Javi, we need</i>
<i> to talk to Layton.</i>

39:40.214 --> 39:43.115
- [breath shaking]

39:44.018 --> 39:45.818
<i> Javi, do you read me?</i>

39:45.952 --> 39:48.420
<i> [tense music]</i>

39:48.555 --> 39:49.822
<i> Javi.</i>

39:49.956 --> 39:51.756
<i> [dog barks]</i>

39:51.758 --> 39:54.159
Shit. He's not responding.

39:54.294 --> 39:56.094
Alex, I'm packing up.

39:56.096 --> 39:57.696
- We have to figure this out.

39:57.832 --> 39:59.163
<i> - I'm gonna meet you inside</i>

39:59.165 --> 40:01.700
<i> to power down and disconnect.</i>

40:01.702 --> 40:03.568
- You won't find the answer
in that screen.

40:03.570 --> 40:05.504
- Well, I don't have time
to pull up the floor

40:05.639 --> 40:07.573
and check every
hydraulic line, do I?

40:07.707 --> 40:11.543
ient music]

40:11.545 --> 40:15.147
Come with me.
We'll look together.

40:15.149 --> 40:16.748
- [panting]

40:16.884 --> 40:18.150
Alex, get up.

40:18.285 --> 40:19.818
- I can't.
- You can do this.

40:19.953 --> 40:22.321
- I can't.
- Why not?

40:23.957 --> 40:26.224
- 'Cause.

40:26.360 --> 40:29.094
'Cause Wilford
taught me how to see.

40:29.229 --> 40:31.029
He taught me how to do this.

40:31.031 --> 40:33.365
I can't do it without him.

40:35.836 --> 40:38.103
Because I miss him.

40:38.972 --> 40:42.974
He murdered you and I miss him.
What is wrong with me?

40:43.110 --> 40:46.512
[sobbing]
What is wrong with me?

40:46.646 --> 40:48.714
I hate him.
- It's okay.

40:50.918 --> 40:52.184
It's okay.

40:52.186 --> 40:54.853
- [sobbing] I hate him so much.

40:54.988 --> 40:57.989
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:58.125 --> 41:02.994
It's okay to miss him
and to hate him.

41:02.996 --> 41:06.064
You know what?

41:06.200 --> 41:08.334
It's even okay to love him.

41:08.468 --> 41:11.537
<i> [emotional, atmospheric music]</i>

41:11.671 --> 41:12.871
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:13.006 --> 41:17.609
I ran from him
and I became him.

41:19.947 --> 41:22.948
Face him.

41:23.083 --> 41:26.285
Face all the things
that haunt you.

41:28.155 --> 41:30.556
It'll set you free.

41:30.690 --> 41:36.828
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:36.964 --> 41:40.099
[footsteps approaching]

41:47.241 --> 41:48.774
- To be an Engineer,

41:48.909 --> 41:53.379
one has to learn to see
beyond the surface of things.

42:01.922 --> 42:08.794
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:16.270 --> 42:20.872
Look beyond the walls
and the floor.

42:20.874 --> 42:23.942
See the arteries
running through them--

42:23.944 --> 42:26.478
<i> the Engine's pulse.</i>

42:29.349 --> 42:32.284
You see the lungs?

42:32.286 --> 42:35.821
Now let them breathe.

42:35.956 --> 42:42.828
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:48.902 --> 42:50.035
- I see it.

42:50.170 --> 42:57.343
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:06.586 --> 43:09.655
- Alex, I told you
we have gotta get off--

43:09.789 --> 43:12.057
- When the car froze over,
the leak in the hydraulic line

43:12.192 --> 43:13.659
affected the frost pattern.

43:13.793 --> 43:15.193
Do you see it?

43:15.195 --> 43:16.795
- Yep.

43:16.930 --> 43:19.131
[banging]

43:19.266 --> 43:20.999
- [panting]

43:21.134 --> 43:23.201
[device beeping]

43:23.203 --> 43:25.203
[mechanical clanging]

43:25.339 --> 43:27.673
[whirring]

43:29.543 --> 43:31.276
- You did it.

43:31.411 --> 43:33.379
[whirring]

43:36.416 --> 43:38.416
- It's free.

43:38.418 --> 43:41.653
<i> [emotional music]</i>

43:45.092 --> 43:48.260
[engine whirring]
[train creaking]

43:57.704 --> 43:59.304
- Wilford is in
critical condition,

43:59.439 --> 44:01.640
but Pelton thinks
he'll pull through.

44:01.642 --> 44:05.243
- There is no getting rid
of the old bastard, is there?

44:05.379 --> 44:07.179
- Yeah, I gotta go
deal with that.

44:07.314 --> 44:09.514
- Same.

44:09.516 --> 44:12.217
- You should some sleep.
- Not yet.

44:13.854 --> 44:15.854
- Good night.
- Night.

44:15.990 --> 44:18.857
<i> [somber music]</i>

44:18.993 --> 44:26.131
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:31.005 --> 44:32.671
- [grunts]

44:32.673 --> 44:35.874
That's not your color, teal.

44:35.876 --> 44:39.011
- You know what? I, uh--

44:39.146 --> 44:41.313
I try and make it work.

44:42.216 --> 44:44.149
I've gotta get going.
It's, uh--

44:44.284 --> 44:46.018
gotta get to work.

44:46.153 --> 44:53.325
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:54.428 --> 44:58.230
Right. Well, uh,
I'll see you around, Mr. Pike.

45:00.767 --> 45:02.967
- Yeah.

45:02.969 --> 45:04.837
Ciao. See you, Ruth.

45:04.971 --> 45:11.844
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:21.922 --> 45:23.988
[knocks on door]

45:23.990 --> 45:26.991
<i> [somber music continues]</i>

45:26.993 --> 45:33.265
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:42.943 --> 45:46.144
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:46.280 --> 45:49.147
[monitor beeping]

45:49.283 --> 45:56.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:58.959 --> 46:00.825
- He's not so powerful
when you put him

46:00.961 --> 46:02.761
into perspective, is he?

46:02.763 --> 46:05.731
[monitor beeping]

46:24.851 --> 46:27.185
<i> [tense music]</i>

46:27.321 --> 46:34.460
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
